As he worked his way up the wall, Cody's shoulder brushed against something. He froze, then cautiously touched it. "A
sconce," he said, and smiled. "When is a sconce not a sconce?" he asked, as he pushed, pulled, and twisted the metal
ring. "When it isn't holding a torch. Then, it's either scrap metal, or," he continued, as one last twist was rewarded
with the sound of a grinding noise in front of him, "it's something else entirely."
